    },
    {
      "id": 2,
      "text": "The Holly Hill History Museum, a grassroots triumph, opened its doors after local businesses and the city rallied for a cultural hub.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        8,
        9,
        10
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 2"
      ],
      "source": "https://www.wonderfulmuseums.com/museum/holly-hill-history-museum/"
    },
    {
      "id": 3,
      "text": "Inside the museum, exhibits weave personal stories into the town’s history, making the past feel tangible and compelling.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        1,
        6
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 2"
      ],
      "source": "https://www.wonderfulmuseums.com/museum/holly-hill-history-museum/"
    },
    {
      "id": 4,
      "text": "Holly Hill sits entirely on Florida’s mainland, unlike neighboring Daytona Beach and Ormond Beach, which straddle the Halifax River’s barrier island.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        15
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Holly_Hill%2C_Florida"
    },
    {
      "id": 5,
      "text": "City parks and river access along the Halifax River offer dog‑friendly recreation and scenic views for residents and visitors alike.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        13
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 1"
      ],
      "source": "https://www.floridavisiting.com/list/holly-hill/"
    },
    {
      "id": 6,
      "text": "The town’s name, Holly Hill, reflects the early settlers’ fondness for the local holly plants that grew on the gentle rise.",
